summary: In a shocking upset at the 2024 US Open, Thanasi Kokkinakis defeated No. 11 seed Stefanos Tsitsipas in their first-round match. With its fast-paced action, stunning visuals, and a star-studded cast, the "Sonic the Hedgehog 3" trailer promises to be a thrilling ride for fans of all ages.

name: Mariah Carey
summary: On an emotionally devastating day, renowned singer Mariah Carey has revealed the heartbreaking news that both her mother, Patricia, and sister, Alison, passed away on the same day. Expressing her sorrow through an exclusive statement provided to PEOPLE magazine, Carey stated that her heart is "broken," describing the loss as "unbearable." Various news outlets, including CTV News, Global News, BBC.com, USA TODAY, and The Guardian, have reported the tragic incident. Times Union further specifies that Carey's sister, Alison, passed away in Coxsackie at the age of 63. Carey's announcement has left her fans and the entertainment world mourning the loss of two beloved members of her family.

name: Star Wars Outlaws
summary: The reviews for "Star Wars: Outlaws" vary widely, with some praising its lore-heavy story, open-world gameplay, and fun combat, while others criticize its repetitive missions, technical issues, and unoriginal gameplay. Forbes compares it to "Assassin's Creed" and "Far Cry," noting similarities in its stealth and exploration mechanics. Shacknews highlights the character of Nix, praising her charisma and the game's focus on her personal journey. GameSpot finds the game "missing the mark," with its weak story, shallow characters, and uninspired gameplay. GamesHub, on the other hand, praises its "fun" and "engaging" gameplay, while Inverse acknowledges its flaws but still deems it a "stunning" open-world experience. The Guardian calls it "a love letter to lore, Lucas, and laser guns," highlighting its faithfulness to the Star Wars universe. Polygon praises its unique setting and gameplay, which they say offers a different perspective on the Star Wars universe. MMORPG.com finds it "a slice of Star Wars we don't often see," while TheGamer compares it to "Watch Dogs" and "Uncharted," praising its stealth and exploration elements. Rock Paper Shotgun, however, gives it a lukewarm review, calling it "a perfectly ok bit of Star Wars."
